clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the treatment of tardive dyskinesia in adults FDA Label

contraindications.disease: No carcinogenicity mutagenicity or impairment of fertility has been observed FDA Label QT prolongation may occur with strong CYP2D6 or CYP3A4 inhibitors or in people who are poor CYP2D6 metabolizers No overdose information is currently available
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Valbenazine decreases the availability of monoamine neurotransmitters by preventing their storage in synaptic vesicles A19221 This is believed to be the reason behind its therapeutic effect in tardive dyskinesia although the exact mechanism is unknown
